ups"--

Contains an edition of Yefet’s Judaeo-Arabic Judaeo-Arabic translation and commentary on Proverbs, including his introduction to the book, based on 13 distinct Mss. as represented in 15 separately-catalogued items. The edited text alternates between Hebrew script and Arabic script depending on the basic Ms. employed. Berlin, Staatsbibliothek, Or. Qu. 828 is incorrectly listed as Or. Qu. 282 on p. 141.</note></biblStruct><bibl type="formatted" subtype="https://www.zotero.org/styles/chicago-note-bibliography-16th-edition">
